APPENDIX E: RUNBOOK TEMPLATE FOR AN ML MODEL
# Runbook: &lt;model name&gt; v&lt;X.Y.Z&gt;
Owners: &lt;team&gt;
On-call: &lt;pager rotation&gt;
Service: &lt;kserve namespace&gt;/&lt;service&gt;

## SLOs
- p99 latency &lt; 100ms
- 5xx &lt; 0.1%
- Drift PSI (top-10 features, 24h) &lt; 0.2
- Calibration ECE &lt; 0.05

## Dashboards
- Grafana: &lt;link&gt;
- Evidently report: &lt;link&gt;
- Cost: &lt;link&gt;

## Alerts → Actions
- HighLatency → scale replicas; check feature store latency; check GPU util
- HighErrorRate → check upstream feature store; check model load; rollback if recent deploy
- DriftPSI &gt; 0.25 → trigger investigation; consider retraining
- AccuracyDrop &gt; 1pp → trigger retrain + champion/challenger comparison

## Rollback (≤5 min)
1. `kubectl set image deploy/&lt;svc&gt; server=&lt;previous-digest&gt;` OR
2. Flip `model.alias=prod` in MLflow registry to previous version
3. Verify by curl /healthz and synthetic eval
4. Post in #incidents; open postmortem ticket

## Promotion (canary)
1. Open PR, pass CI (tests + behavioral + fairness)
2. Shadow for 24h
3. Canary 1% → 5% → 25% → 100% with 30m holds
4. Auto-rollback if HighErrorRate or DriftPSI

## Data dependencies
- Source tables: &lt;list&gt;
- Feature view: &lt;name&gt;
- Schemas: &lt;links&gt;

## Compliance
- Model card: &lt;link&gt;
- Last audit: &lt;date&gt;
- PII handling: &lt;summary&gt;
